text: This really hit home.  My heart strings are pulled.  Last year I caught my wife of 13 years with another man.  My kids and I walked in on her at a restaurant. My older son who is now 12 stared crying immediately. I walked them back to the car and headed back in for an explanation..... she said I was not making enough money anymore. I went from 119k to 26k annually. I filled for divorce 48 hours after the event....  I was raised by a wonderful mother. My parents are still together to this day. Divorce affects the children.  -----------And revenge..?  Well that's not in my hands.  I miss my boys.  Statistics show that they will not be successful in life.  I will not give up on them.   50% custody. She still wants to party at 40 years of age....  I have built my empire without her. I can do it again.....  a good woman will stick by her man no matter what happens

text: This is a sad sad example of a father.  Being a father is more that just providing food, clothing, and shelter. Yes, a father is supposed to love and like his children. What father wouldn't?  A child has to learn emotional and social development not only from the mother but also from the father as well.  And if he can't provide that then he needs to step out of the picture.  A child is more than just a body to feed and clothe.  A child, girls and boys have feelings and emotions.  Part of some of the ills of out society is precisely because the father was not there to provide for the critical emotional support that children need.  A child brought up in an environment where he is not felt loved and supported could turn out to be a criminal or a monster.  I have never seen a child raised up without a supportive father that did not have some kind of serious defect in their personality.

text: A lot of promising Oscar contenders this year - Manchester by the Sea, Nocturnal animals, La La Land, Miss Sloane, Collateral Beauty, The Founder, Silence, Gold.  But I gotta admit, I'm looking forward to and rooting for Fences the most. A small, but powerful story with great actors. I'd love for this to be so good, it wins an Oscar for best picture, best director, best actor and best actress.   And for all the circus Will Smith and co. made last year about black filmmakers not being nominated, I didn't want Smith or Spike Lee or the NWA guys to be nominated last year, because they didn't deserve it IMO. But if this is as good as the trailer suggests, I'm rooting for Denzel and co. to win. So really, the color of skin has nothing to do with anything and these jilted celebrities should stop making stupid excuses when they don't make a movie that warrants a nomination.

The film was adapted from 2 theater plays on Broadway, so I'm sure that the performances are mastered. The authenticity is also incredibly well crafted. Denzel and Viola are great together--this is going to be a powerhouse film I'm sure of it.

text: I think that we've seen this story so many times. Why are black people so often (it feels like most movies do this) in pain, struggling, barely getting by, beating the odds, surviving on luck, and then finally a happy ending. We know what's going to happen. We know how the story is going to end. There's The Butler, The Great Debaters, The Pursuit of Happiness, The Help, The Color Purple, The Grave Diggers Daughter, Chiraq, and 12 Years a Slave. For the sake of story telling, shouldn't we have more movies that show black people in different roles? Shouldn't black folks be entitled to have a good time? I bet they're going to nominate this movie for an Academy Award, because these types of movies are the only ones that will get nominated.  I'm not a Madea fan, but Tyler Perry is very successful despite his bad ratings from critics. He realizes that black people (and all people) want to laugh and have a good time. I don't see his success as a coincidence; he recognized a want that has been so largely ignored by Hollywood.

Danzel plays a character who is selfish, very self centered and alcoholic, who spends the first  20 minutes of the movie, in a mild state of rage, as he continuously rambling on and on about how HE is being cheated out of a position at his job that he deserves. The character is bitter and he lets everyone feel his bitter wrath.  The main character is very unlikable, bordering on being a narcissistic alcoholic who dominates every conversation.  The writers of this movie could have done a better job of making the main character more likable by giving him some good joking lines, maybe like a Fred Sanford type persona.  Unfortunately, this movie will resonate with too many  women who were married to hardworking man who were insensitive or whose father was neglectful or abusive.

The reality of marriages that stand the test of time and life as depicted here when Denzel not only had an affair but got the other woman pregnant AND was man enough to tell his wife about it, rather than hide it deny the innocent baby coming into the world. This movie does indeed tell the raw dynamics of the human experience and if you're a person that believes in God you can clearly see the tones of FAITH present throughout this story. Great Job Denzel Washington # Director

text: فيلم دراما رومانسي جميل قصته عن : رجل زنجي ، وظيفته جامع قمامة ، يكافح في حياته لأجل لقمة عيشه ، مع الظروف القاسية التي تحيط به من : العنصرية مع الزنوج ، وفقدانه لحنان الأب والأم في طفولته ، وتربيته لأولاده ، ومراعاته لزوجته ، وحمايته لأخيه المختل عقلياً ، وظغوط العمل ، وغيرها من أمور الحياة . تطرق الفيلم لعدة قضايا : ١- العنصرية ضد الزنوج . ٢- العمل بأي وظيفة لأجل كسب لقمة حلال . ٣- إعتماد دول الغرب على أبنائهم في الوظائف ، حتى في وظيفة جامع القمامة ، وعدم الإستعانة بالعمالة الأجنبية . ٤- أهمية دور الأب في حياة العائلة . ٥- أهمية دور الأم في حياة العائلة . ٦- الحمل الثقيل والأكبر يقع على كاهل الأب . ٧- حرمان الأب لأبنائه من رغباتهم ، لأجل تربيتهم ، وإعتمادهم على أنفسهم ، والحصول على ما هو أفضل وأعظم . ٨- قسوة الأب على الأبناء تنبع من الشفقة عليهم . ٩- الصديق وقت الضيق . ١٠- أهمية الصديق في الحياة : لأجل مناقشة مصاعب الحياة ، وكيفية التغلب عليها ، والبحث عن حل المشاكل العائلية ، والفضفضة له عن الهموم والألام ، التي لا يستطيع التحدث بها أمام العائلة . ١١- إخلاص الرجل في حياته لعائلته : فيوفر لهم كل شيء ، وكل سبل الراحة ، رغم المكابدة والمعاناة اليومية في الحياة . ١٢- إخلاص الزوجة لزوجها وأبنائها : في رعايتهم ، وإطعامهم ، وإسباغ الحنان عليهم ، والبحث عن الأعذار لهم ، وتحمل قسوتهم . ١٣- النزوة عند الرجل ، ولا علاقة لها بالحب ، فعند النصاري تكون : بالزنى ، وفِي الإسلام تكون : بالزواج من أربع نساء . ١٤- غيرة المرأة ، وهي كالنار تحرقها ، وتبكيها . ١٥- الجنس ضرورة بشرية ، حتى ولو بلغ الرجل الستين من عمره . ١٦- الزوجة المخلصة تبقى مع زوجها ، مهما حدث وجرى وكان ، من فقرٍ ، أو بيت صغير ، أو عدم تحقيق رغباتها ، أو خيانة الزوج . ١٧- الحبيب يتحمل الحبيب ، ولا يفرط فيه ، ويتمسك به رغم كل الظروف . ١٨- لأجل عين تكرم ألف عين : كما حدث في هذه القصة : عندما قامت الزوجة بتربية أبنة عشيقة زوجها ، لأجل خاطره وإرضائه . ١٩- تربية الأبناء من أصعب أمور الحياة . ٢٠- رابطة الأخوة لا تنمحي ولا تموت ، حتى ولو كانت من غير أشقاء . ٢١- صلة الدم أقوى من الألم : كحال الأخوة غير الأشقاء ، رغم غيرتهم لأمهم ، لكن دمهم أقوى منها . ٢٢- صلة الأقارب . ٢٣- الرأفة بالمختل عقلياً ، ومراعاة خاطره ، وذلك بعدم إدخاله المستشفى . ٢٤- قضاء وقت الفراغ في الهواية التي يحبها الشخص . ٢٥- الحياة العسكرية ولاءٌ للوطن . ٢٦- وجود الرب والدين في حياة الإنسان . ٢٧- أهتمام الزنوج بالكنيسة وتقاليدها أكثر من البيض . ٢٨- النصارى أرق قلوباً وأفئدة بخلاف المغضوب عليهم . ٢٩- الملل من الروتين اليومي . ٣٠- الموت قدر ، وكل شَيْءٍ مكتوب بقدر .

text: Denzel Washington is one of my favorite actors. But this movie was definitely not role model cool. If anything, Denzel's portrayal of Troy Maxson was that of a self centered arrogant jerk. And although Viola Davis mentioned that her role in this film elevates women, I am still scratching my head. If it's about income equality, yes, I agree. But Davis' portrayal of a faithful woman in the film despite Troy having an affair outside of the marriage sort of put women in the stone age. It's as if a woman's role is to accept a man's deficiencies when they occur right in your face. And yes, I get that a lot of women cheat on men during marriages too - no one is perfect. But being specific about this movie, it makes black women in general appear to be at the lowest level on the evolution hierarchical human chain.

text: Good movie. Lot's of dialogue...not like most modern movies. I understand people have both positive and negative traits and gaining empathy for the terrible life experiences this man had helps you to forgive and love him despite bad behavior. In addition, he was a good provider. But he was NOT a good father or husband and he did not care. He was controlling more than loving. I saw no concern on his part for how others felt or what they wanted. I still have a hard time thinking this sends a good message to women. For her to stay with him when he informed her how it would be ...that he would continue his affair...and then foist his problem on her....not a good role model.  I understand she was financially dependent, that she loved him, and that she wanted to care for the child. But I would not sleep with him, cook for him, clean his house, or even talk to him. He would be INFORMED of my rules. If his choice was to not come home and not be present, then my job would be to control the money and to care for the child. PERIOD. In addition, she should begin socializing with other men as a single woman.
